
  <sn><md>### Spectroscopy

Spectroscopy is the scientific technique used to study `how matter interacts with electromagnetic radiation` (light). It is one of the most powerful analytical tools in physics, chemistry, soil science, astronomy, medicine, and environmental studies. By observing how materials absorb, transmit, reflect, or emit light, we can determine their `composition, structure, and physical properties`.

